commText: Prabhsimran and Bairstow are at the crease. Prabhsimran is on strike. Chameera will open the attack
Chameera to Prabhsimran, leg byes, 1 run, I0$ short of length delivery, Prabhsimran is beaten on the inside edge and struck around the tummy. The ball rolls to point and Bairstow calls him through
Chameera to Bairstow, 1 run, I0$ back of a length around off, Bairstow ekes out an inside edge onto the pad and the ball rolls to point
Chameera to Prabhsimran, 1 run, cramps Prabhsimran for room with an in-angler, tucked away backward of square leg

Chameera to Bairstow, FOUR, in the air but in the gap. On a length and outside off, Bairstow looks to drive on the rise but mistimes it wide of cover, not off the middle but the fast outfield does the job
Chameera to Bairstow, 1 run, 145.3ks back of a length around off, Bairstow angles it through backward point
Chameera to Prabhsimran, no run, fullish delivery around off, Prabhsimran defends with a straight bat
Harshit Rana, right-arm fast medium, comes into the attack
Harshit Rana to Bairstow, no run, fraction short and outside off, Bairstow reaches and chops it back to Salt
One slip for Rana as well
Harshit Rana to Bairstow, leg byes, 1 run, slower ball and it grips, Bairstow is through the shot early and is beaten on the inside edge, struck on the pad and the ball rolls to the off-side
Harshit Rana to Prabhsimran, SIX, shot! I0$ full delivery on leg-stump, Prabhsimran flicks it stylishly and sends the ball sailing over deep square leg
Harshit Rana to Prabhsimran, no run, good length ball around off, Prabhsimran knocks it to cover
Harshit Rana to Prabhsimran, SIX, short of length delivery, Prabhsimran arches back and upper cuts it towards deep backward point. There was a fielder but he could only watch the ball sail over him
Harshit Rana to Prabhsimran, 1 run, slower short of length delivery, tucked to mid-wicket and Prabhsimran retains strike

Chameera to Prabhsimran, SIX, nicely done! Prabhsimran shuffles across, crouches and laps it over fine leg, just clearing the rope. This was bowled at I0$ informs Ravi Shastri on air and Prabhsimran used the pace smartly
Chameera to Prabhsimran, no run, on a length and outside off, Prabhsimran crunches it straight to cover-point

Chameera to Prabhsimran, FOUR, this time goes aerial. Very similar to the previous delivery and Prabhsimran pumps it over extra cover, one bounce and over the ropes. Chameera is bowling quick but is disappearing even quicker

Chameera to Prabhsimran, SIX, I0$ slower ball and Prabhsimran has spotted it right out of the hand, just a tad delay in the bat swing and that is enough for him to middle the loft, sends it sailing over long-off
Chameera to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, I0$ off-pace delivery, Prabhsimran nudges it to square leg and races back for the second
Chameera to Prabhsimran, wide, sprays the slower ball outside off, Prabhsimran tries to cut but can't connect
Chameera to Prabhsimran, FOUR, 23 off the over. Just what Punjab needed. Another slower ball and Prabhsimran gives the charge, thumps it straight back over Chameera for a one bounce four
KKR have used their impact sub - Venky Iyer goes off and Anukul Roy comes in.. Shreyas Iyer sent the message that he needs Anukul during Chameera's over
Anukul Roy, Left arm orthodox, comes into the attack
Anukul Roy to Bairstow, no run, fraction short and around off, Bairstow cuts and picks out cover-point
Anukul Roy to Bairstow, FOUR, once more pushed through flatter, Bairstow makes room and punches it in front of square on the off-side
Anukul Roy to Bairstow, 1 run, I0$ fired full on the stumps, Bairstow backs away and drills it to extra cover where Russell makes a half stop
Anukul Roy to Prabhsimran, FOUR, flighted outside off, Prabhsimran makes room and throws his bat on the inside out loft, slices it over backward point and the ball lands safely, rolls into the rope
Anukul Roy to Prabhsimran, 2 runs, now tries the reverse sweep and miscues it towards cover, the ball goes in the gap and the pair pick up a brace
Anukul Roy to Prabhsimran, 1 run, drifting in with the angle, Prabhsimran nudges it into the mid-wicket pocket
Sunil Narine, right-arm off break, comes into the attack
Narine to Prabhsimran, FOUR, Narine greeted with a boundary. Prabhsimran shuffles across, kneels down and sweeps it over backward square leg

Narine to Prabhsimran, SIX, fifty for Prabhsimran. It has come off 18 balls and the Punjab dugout are on their feet applauding. This knock has given Punjab the perfect start. He once again moves across, gets inside the line and sweeps it into the crowd this time
Narine to Prabhsimran, no run, short of length and cramping Prabhsimran, he chops it to backward point
Narine to Prabhsimran, 1 run, nudged to square leg
Narine to Bairstow, no run, flatter delivery around off, Bairstow knocks it to cover and searches for a single, not there
Narine to Bairstow, 1 run, slower and spinning in, Bairstow looks to sweep and gets an under-edge to short fine
Anukul Roy to Bairstow, FOUR, streaky! Fired full on off, Bairstow swings across the line and squirts an inside edge to fine leg

Fastest IPL fifties for PBKS (by balls taken) 14 - KL Rahul vs DC, Mohali, 2018 17 - Nicholas Pooran vs SRH, Dubai, 2020 18 - Prabhsimran Singh vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 19 - David Miller vs RR, Sharjah, 2014 19 - KL Rahul vs CSK, Mohali, 2019

Anukul Roy to Bairstow, SIX, monster hit! This was what he was looking for on the previous ball, Bairstow connects this time and the ball travels a long way into the deep mid-wicket crowd. 97-meter six..

Anukul Roy to Bairstow, FOUR, shorter, flatter and outside off, Bairstow reaches and slaps it over extra cover. The bottom hand comes off the bat handle and the ball too came off the toe-end, but the ball still reached the fence
Anukul Roy to Bairstow, FOUR, full pitcher around leg, Bairstow makes a bit of room and whips it wide of mid-on. There's no stopping that..
Anukul Roy to Bairstow, SIX, wow! Bairstow is turning it on now. He was nowhere close to the ball but just went through with the shot, got the height an distance to clear the wide long-on fence
Run-out check sent upstairs. Prabhsimran is struggling. He's short of the crease. OUT
Anukul Roy to Bairstow, THATS OUT!! Run Out!!

Anukul Roy to Bairstow, out Prabhsimran Run Out!! Needless! Prabhsimran knows that. He throws his head back and walks back dejected. There was never a single. Bairstow looks to heave and squirts an inside edge to short fine, Prabhsimran called for a risky single and paid the price. Narine can't do no wrong this season. He's scoring runs, picking wickets and now scoring direct hits as well. Picked up the ball and hit the target the striker's end, Prabhsimran was well short of the crease. Prabhsimran run out (Narine) 54(20) [4s-4 6s-5]

Over Summary (1-6): -- Prabhsimran slams two sixes off Rana -- Prabhsimran takes 23 runs off Chameera in his second over -- Prabhsimran gets to his fifty off 18 balls -- Bairstow slams three fours and two sixes off Anukul Roy -- Prabhsimran is run-out. Punjab 93 for 1 after 6 overs

Timeout! What a start it has been for Punjab! But that wicket off the last ball of the powerplay might have just given KKR some respite. Prabhsimran was off the blocks in a flash and reached his fifty off 18 balls. Bairstow was a spectator till the last over of the powerplay, he unleashed on Anukul and smashed him for 24 runs. The chase is definitely on..
Rilee Rossouw, left handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Bairstow, no run, short of length and turning in, Bairstow attempts to cut and is beaten on the outside edge
Narine to Bairstow, 1 run, fraction short and outside off, Bairstow cuts square of the wicket
Narine to Rossouw, no run, off-break and it turns away outside off, Rossouw has a waft and is beaten on the outside edge
Narine to Rossouw, no run, now the carrom ball which breaks in, Rossouw knocks it to cover
Narine to Rossouw, no run, offie spins away outside off, Rossouw throws his bat on the slash and misses
Narine to Rossouw, no run, I0$ carrom ball on the stumps, Rossouw makes room and knocks it to cover. Just a single

PBKS batters scoring 50-plus runs within the Powerplay 59*(22) - Jonny Bairstow vs RCB, Brabourne, 2022 55*(23) - KL Rahul vs CSK, Mohali, 2019 54(20) - Prabhsimran Singh vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 52*(23) - Wriddhiman Saha vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2014 51(16) - KL Rahul vs DC, Mohali, 2018 All except Bairstow's came in a run-chase
Harshit Rana [1.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack
Harshit Rana to Bairstow, no run, fraction short and outside off, Bairstow toe-ends the cut to short third

Harshit Rana to Bairstow, SIX, for a moment Bairstow would have thought he picked out the fielder, but the ball sails over. Slower ball on middle, Bairstow scoops it up and gets enough to clear long-on
Harshit Rana to Bairstow, 1 run, very full delivery around off, Bairstow drills it back past Rana and down to long-off
Harshit Rana to Rossouw, FOUR, I0$ short of length delivery, Rossouw loves pace on the ball and was quickly onto the pull, hits it in front of square and beats a sliding Russell near deep mid-wicket
Harshit Rana to Rossouw, 2 runs, I0$ slower ball outside off, Rossouw drags it off the inner half wide of long-on and the pair scamper back
Harshit Rana to Rossouw, 1 run, fullish delivery around off, Rossouw flicks it off the inner half to deep backward square
Varun Chakaravarthy, right-arm leg break, comes into the attack
Chakaravarthy to Rossouw, 2 runs, and slams the slog sweep but the man at deep square stops it despite a fumble. Two more to the tally
Chakaravarthy to Rossouw, 1 run, short, outside off, Rossouw goes back and pulls the ball down to long-on for a single
Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, 1 run, Bairstow still going at more than 200! Wanted to slog sweep but played it too fine. Didn't time it. One bounce and the man at deep backward did well to stop it
Chakaravarthy to Rossouw, 1 run, slaps that off the back foot and down to long-off for a single

Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, SIX, and one-handed mistimed sixer! Fifty for Bairstow on come back. Needed some luck. I0$ Was a flatter one, outside off, Bairstow threw a hand at it and sliced it. The man at long-off flung himself to his left and got hands to it but the ball popped out as he fell on the cushion at the fence. Bairstow is chuffed but job is half done
Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, 1 run, tucks it down with soft hands into the on-side for a single as it turned in
Andre Russell, right-arm fast, comes into the attack
Russell to Bairstow, no run, back of a length delivery, decks in, Bairstow backs away and dabs the ball down to short third man
Russell to Bairstow, FOUR, short, slower, Bairstow waits on it and pulls that in a controlled manner behind square for a four. The man at fine leg was inside the circle and he was beaten easily
For the first time in IPL history, both openers from either side have registered a 50-plus score in a match, the 11th such instance in Men's T20 cricket.
Russell to Bairstow, 1 run, fuller ball, outside off, gets an inside edge. He has had a few of these tonight. Gets it down to long leg for a single
Russell to Rossouw, SIX, and six more. That was a buffet ball. Dropped short, outside off, Rossouw got hold of it and pulled it over deep mid. Superb hit indeed as he timed that well
Russell to Rossouw, 1 run, length delivery angled across, Rossouw slaps that down to long-on for a single. The fielder did well to dive to his right and stop it
Russell to Bairstow, no run, dot ball to end the over just the way it started. Was a slower short ball, Bairstow looked to pull it and cue-ended it down to the keeper. Was too early into the shot
Chakaravarthy to Rossouw, 1 run, gets it down to long-off for a single as that was a flatter one outside off. Punjab are half way there
Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, no run, what happened there? The ball spun away from him when he thought it would turn in. In an embarrassing manner, lets it go to the keeper
Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, no run, and looks to slog sweep but misses as the ball turned away. He had no clues about the turn on that one. The ball ripped away and Bairstow missed it by a mile
Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, SIX, flatter one, outside off, Bairstow almost sliced it and sent it well over long-off. This is brutal hitting from the batters tonight

Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, FOUR, straight down the ground for a four. Fifty of the partnership is up as well. Was a fuller ball. Bairstow got under it and slammed it down the ground. He didn't have to bother about the turn and just let his sinews do the rest

Bairstow wants a drink. Little pause in play. It is humid in Kolkata. Not easy for the players even during the evenings. But kudos to Bairstow for having scored 67 off 32 in his come back game. He has had some luck but has done well to sail through so far. His power game has helped him.

Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, SIX, I0$ Whoa. That was short, Bairstow looked to pull and seemed like a top-edge. But the ball went sailing over deep square. It has gone a mile and Punjab are 149 for 1 after 11 overs

Highest scores after first 10 overs of an IPL innings 158/4 - SRH vs DC, Delhi, 2024 148/2 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 141/2 - MI vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2024 138/4 - DC vs SRH, Delhi, 2024 137/0 - KKR vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024 135/1 - KKR vs DC, Visakhapatnam, 2024 132/1 - PBKS vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 131/3 - PBKS vs SRH, Hyderabad, 2014 This is PBKS's highest IPL score at the 10-over mark in the IPL, bettering 131/3 against SRH in Hyderabad in 2014.
Russell to Rossouw, wide, slower, shorter, goes over the batter and Rossouw let it go. Easy call of a wide

Russell to Rossouw, SIX, length delivery, swiped across the line for a sixer. Massive hit. This is some hitting. The balls are flying at will and that too well over the fences. Again for a second it looked like he was early into the shot but managed to wood it well
Russell to Rossouw, wide, slower, well wide outside off and has been left alone for it to be wided
Russell to Rossouw, 1 run, drills it down to long-on for a single as the bowler managed to zero in on the yorker at the boot of the batter
Russell to Bairstow, SIX, length delivery, angled in, on the pads, Bairstow helps himself to another sixer. Was sent over deep backward square. Now thye need less than a 100

Russell to Bairstow, SIX, please distribute crash helmets with the tickets. There has to be some warning. That's another massive six. Short ball, angled in, Bairstow pivoted a little and smashed it over deep square. Easy pickings. He is seeing the ball like a beach ball for sure. 85 off 35 for Bairstow
Russell to Bairstow, 2 runs, fuller ball, outside off, drilled wide of deep cover for a couple more

Russell to Bairstow, 1 run, hoicked across the line and finds the man at deep mid. Only a single. 89 needed off 8 overs. This is Punjab's game to lose I feel from here on as the wicket seems to be a belter. The average today has been a six per over. That's scary for bowlers
Sunil Narine [2.0-0-13-0] is back into the attack

Narine to Bairstow, FOUR, oh stop it! Narine concedes a four now. Bairstow into the 90s. Was short, outside off, Bairstow sits back and slaps the cut past point for a four. He is batting like a dream. So easy!!!
Narine to Bairstow, 1 run, slams it square of the wicket for a single as that was short again. The man at sweeper cover this time cuts it off. Rossouw back on strike
Narine to Rossouw, THATS OUT!! Caught!!

Narine to Rossouw, out Caught by Shreyas Iyer!! Finally KKR have a wicket. That was floated well outside off and Rossouw went for the slog sweep but managed a huge top-edge. The man at cover got under it and took it easily. Second wicket falls. Good little cameo from Rossouw ends. That was away from him and he failed to control the shot. The ball turned away as well and I don't think he picked that either. Rossouw c Shreyas Iyer b Narine 26(16) [4s-1 6s-2]
Shashank Singh, right handed bat, comes to the crease
Narine to Shashank Singh, no run, the finisher is here! Starts by playing out a dot. Flatter and pushed back to the bowler. Wanted to nudge it down
Narine to Shashank Singh, no run, flatter one, turns away, Shashank Singh looks to dab it down and misses. Still 84 needed now off 43 balls

Narine to Shashank Singh, 1 run, stays inside the line of the delivery and tucks it down for a single. How much say has Narine had on this game? He scored those runs in no time and now with the ball has been a cut above everyone. His three overs so far have been priceless for KKR

Over Summary (7-13): -- Narine just concedes a single in the 7th over -- Bairstow brings up his fifty off 23 balls -- The 50-run stand comes up between Bairstow and Rossouw -- Russell is smashed for 24 runs in his 2nd over -- Narine breaks the partnership, Rossouw holes out
Varun Chakaravarthy [2.0-0-29-0] is back into the attack

Chakaravarthy to Shashank Singh, SIX, and six more! Fuller one, Shashank Singh sits down and slams the slog sweep over deep square. Huge hit indeed from Shashank Singh as he got under it and put it away with elan
Chakaravarthy to Shashank Singh, SIX, take that! Was waiting on the back foot. Chakaravarthy bowled it short, Shashank Singh slammed it over deep mid. He is toying with the mind of the bowler
Chakaravarthy to Shashank Singh, 2 runs, takes it from the sticks and nudges it wide of short fine for a couple of runs
Chakaravarthy to Shashank Singh, 1 run, stays his crease and nudges it down to deep mid for a single
Chakaravarthy to Bairstow, 1 run, and one more. 67 needed now. Was a short ball, well wide as well. Bairstow cue-ended it down to long-off for a single

Chakaravarthy to Shashank Singh, 1 run, need 66 off 6. You have to back Punjab. Was a leading edge and went over the bowler as he leapt up. The batter eas a little early into the shot as he tried to clip it. Chakaravarthy has gone for 46 off 3 overs
Narine to Shashank Singh, 1 run, one more. Will they play out Narine? Walked across and tucked it uppishly down to deep mid for a single
Narine to Bairstow, 1 run, on to 95 now. Fuller ball, Bairstow drills it down to long-on. He didn't get the elevation
Narine to Shashank Singh, no run, 64 now off 33 balls. That turned away, Shashank Singh looked to defend and was beaten on the outer-edge. The keeper whipped the bails off but he was in

Narine to Shashank Singh, no run, backs away, looks to loft it over cover and misses. The keeper whipped the bails off again. But Shashank Singh was back I guess in his crease. He did drag it out as the ball missed his inside edge. Nothing on UltraEdge. Then the keeper whipped the bails off but he had dragged it back
Narine to Shashank Singh, 1 run, stays back and stabs it down into the off-side for a single. 63 needed off 31 balls now. What a spell this has been? He has been magical tonight
Narine to Bairstow, 2 runs, turns it down on to the on-side for a brace.
Time-out. Punjab have done well to allow Narine finish his spell without causing much damage. 61 needed off 5 overs and that too on a belter. Punjab should get over the line I feel.
Harshit Rana [2.0-0-27-0] is back into the attack
Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, FOUR, takes a few steps down and slaps it past point for a four. The man at point failed to stop it
Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, 1 run, walks across his sticks and tucks it down to deep mid for a single as the ball angled in

Harshit Rana to Bairstow, no run, slower delivery, nips in, Bairstow looks to slog it and misses. That was a slower spinning delivery from Harshit Rana and he managed to disguise it well. Bairstow is batting on 97!
Harshit Rana to Bairstow, 1 run, slower one, outside off, stabbed down into the off-side for a single. He has moved to 98 now...

Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, 1 run, short ball, outside off, Shashank Singh gets on top of the ball and pats it down to deep cover for a single. Got on top of the bounce but failed to place it well

Harshit Rana to Bairstow, 2 runs, 100 for Bairstow! That was a tough chance for the man at deep cover. The fielder at deep cover dived but failed to get under it. In a comeback game, Bairstow has managed to bring up his ton off his 45 balls. That was fuller, well outside off, Bairstow sliced the drive. But the man at deep cover just failed to grab it. Bairstow has had a few tough months but finally something going right for him

Fastest IPL hundreds for PBKS (by balls faced) 38 - David Miller vs RCB, Mohali, 2013 45 - Mayank Agarwal vs RR, Sharjah, 2020 45 - Jonny Bairstow vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 49 - Wriddhiman Saha vs KKR, Bengaluru, 2014 final
Dushmantha Chameera [2.0-0-30-0] is back into the attack

Chameera to Shashank Singh, no run, slower, wide, slapped to the man at cover. Dot ball. 52 needed off 23 balls. Punjab still have this in control. But the last few overs haven't really gone their way
Chameera to Shashank Singh, SIX, slower, wider, fuller, Shashank Singh gets under it and thumps it over deep cover. Massive hit indeed. He is timing them superbly
Chameera to Shashank Singh, no run, superb yorker from round the wicket and Shashank Singh wanted to dab it down but missed it. Was well bowled indeed

Chameera to Shashank Singh, SIX, 40 needed off 20 balls now. Six more. Was a full toss, little higher, the umpire deemed it as a no-ball. But KKR challenged it. The ball was certainly dipping on the batter. He was crouching as well. The third umpire had a look at the graphics. He stayed inside the line of the ball and managed to help it over fine leg. The waist height was 1.06 m but was dipping at 0.73 m. So, it is a legal ball
Chameera to Shashank Singh, no run, fuller ball, outside off, Shashank Singh looks to slam it and gets an edge on it to send it down to the keeper. 40 needed off 19 balls now...

Chameera to Shashank Singh, SIX, story of the over has been sixes and dots in the over. Three sixes and three dots to round off the over. Was a slower short ball and Shashank Singh stayed inside the line of the delivery to thump it over deep mid. This guys is some talent. Fifth six for Shashank Singh
Harshit Rana to Bairstow, 1 run, only a single. Low full toss, carved down to deep cover for a single. 38 sixes have been hit so far! This is insane hitting
Review

Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, wide, Another review for a delivery which hasn't been wided by the umpire. Was a short, slower delivery and Shashank Singh wanted to slap it but missed. The height as well as how wide it was from outside off would be checked. And indeed wided as well

Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, SIX, short ball, thumped over deep mid. 39th sixer off the game. Most in a T20 game. Was a short ball, Shashank Singh got hold of it and picked the bones out of it. 26 needed now

Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, SIX, 40th sixer of the game! 20 needed now. Punjab have this game in their kitty now. Was a short ball, Shashank Singh got inside the line of the delivery and slammed it over deep mid. He is hitting them as clean as a whistle. Fifty for this sensation. He has made them sing his tunes as usual

Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, FOUR, length delivery, wide outside off, Shashank Singh slices it over point. Smashing hit indeed by Shashank Singh as he gets Punjab closer to the target. 16 needed now off 14 balls
Harshit Rana to Shashank Singh, 1 run, fuller length delivery, driven down to deep cover for a single. Punjab scale 247 now. They have made short work of a massive score

Harshit Rana to Bairstow, SIX, Bairstow, where have you been? Gets under the fuller length ball and thumps it over long-off. This is scary. 262 might well be chased down with decent balls to spare. How much can the bowlers be brutalized in this edition? What's the melting point for them? 9 needed now
Ramandeep Singh, right-arm medium, comes into the attack

Ramandeep Singh to Shashank Singh, SIX, straight down the ground for a? You know it. It's another sixer. 3 needed now. Walk in the park so far for Punjab. This is hard to believe. Will be the most bitter pill for KKR to swallow in their IPL history
Ramandeep Singh to Shashank Singh, 1 run, slams it across the line to deep mid for a single. Two needed now
Ramandeep Singh to Bairstow, 1 run, slower, shorter, Bairstow slaps it down to deep point for a single

Ramandeep Singh to Shashank Singh, 1 run, Punjab have successfully scaled down the highest total in T20 history with elan with 8 balls to spare! Eden has witnessed history. Shashank Singh is making a habit of finishing some fascinating games. This is a record chase. Can't wrap my head around this. Freak. Genius. You choose your own adjectives. Was a fuller ball, Shashank Singh drove it down to mid-off for a single. There was a shy at the bowler's end but he missed

23:19 Local Time, 17:49 GMT, 23:19 IST: What do I say? How do I define this? All of you can catch your breathe for starters. Because Prabhsimran started on fast lanes. We thought it will eventually end and it did. He was run-out after his fifty. But Punjab had tallied 93 in the powerplay. Rossouw came in and Bairstow just got going. They had a tough time against Narine and the West Indian got rid of Rossouw. But Shashank Singh came in and the rest as they say was history. He just toyed with the bowlers. He plucked sixes like we pluck apples in an orchard. Bairstow was a happy spectator at the other end. He scored a 100 in his comeback game and Punjab romped home in 18.4 overs. Almost 250 runs came in just sixes! That tells you how hapless the bowlers were. It indeed was bat vs bat and the batters of Punjab have outshone the home team with elan in the end. Punjab were on the brink of elimination coming into this and they have answered everyone doubting their intentions.

Shreyas Iyer | KKR captain: I would have (taken 260 at the start of the day). The way the batters batted was tremendous to see, Sunny coming in.. the way Salt batted, they delivered and it was a treat for the eyes. Both the teams played tremendously, one of those games where you go back to the drawing board and see where it went wrong especially not being able to defend 260. We have to sum up the conditions and come up with better ideas. It is brilliant to see him (Narine) go out there and strike the ball, hopefully he keeps continuing with such performances.

Shashank Singh - When I was in the dug-out, I was just watching the behaviour of the pitch, felt it was coming on nicely with good bounce. Just backed myself to hit the other bowlers, was happy to take the singles and doubles off Narine, we wanted to play him out. He has given me complete freedom (on coach Trevor Bayliss), has told me to play the way I can. A big positive when Jonny (Bairstow) supports you (from the other end), he has played 100 Test matches and to see him clap for you, you'll feel happy and vindicated. We still have 5 matches to go, we'll take it one match at a time and I believe that we can still qualify to the playoffs.

Highest targets successfully chased in Men’s T20 cricket 262 - Punjab Kings vs Kolkata Knight Riders, Kolkata, IPL 2024 259 - South Africa vs West Indies, Centurion, 2023 253 - Middlesex vs Surrey, The Oval, T20 Blast 2023 244 - Australia vs New Zealand, Auckland, 2018 243 - Bulgaria vs Serbia, Sofia, 2022 243 - Multan Sultans vs Peshawar Zalmi, Rawalpindi, PSL 2023
Highest targets successfully chased in the IPL 262 - PBKS vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 224 - RR vs PBKS, Sharjah, 2020 224 - RR vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 219 - MI vs CSK, Delhi, 2021
Highest aggregates in an IPL match 549 - RCB vs SRH, Bengaluru, 2024 523 - SRH vs MI, Hyderabad, 2024 523 - KKR vs PBKS, Kolkata, 2024 469 - CSK vs RR, Chennai, 2010 465 - DC vs SRH, Delhi, 2024

Most sixes in an IPL innings 24 - PBKS vs KKR, Kolkata, 2024 22 - SRH vs RCB, Bengaluru, 2024 22 - SRH vs DC, Delhi, 2024 21 - RCB vs PWI, Bengaluru, 2013 Only Nepal have managed more sixes in an innings in Men’s T20 cricket than PBKS today. KKR bowling today \nNarine: 1/24 from 4 overs (ER: 6) \nOthers: 0/236 from 14.4 overs (ER: 16.09)
Stat round-up by Roshan Gede

Sam Curran | PBKS captain: Very pleasing. Most importantly the win. Cricket is turning into baseball. We have had a few tough weeks. But we hung in there. The way guys train. The confidence and the coaches. The small grounds and the dew. The reviews which might give you an extra ball. We hung in there and managed to chase it down with balls to spare. Pleased for Johnny. What an amazing knock. Shashank Singh has been the find of the tournament for us. Ashutosh as well. Proud of everyone.

Bairstow, Player of the Match: We got off to a good start. That was the key. They got off to a good start as well thanks to Sunil. You have to take risks. Sometimes luck will go your way. Some days it won't be your day. Tried to whack it as far as possible. If it is in your area, you had to go. We had a couple of quiet overs when Sunil was bowling as we knew how important he is for them. Shashank Singh is a special player. The knowledge he has had been amazing. How clean he hit it! Was indeed very special.

Yesterday RCB and tonight PBKS, the laggards have started their ascendancy. There is nothing called favorites in the IPL and we had another example of it. Punjab were culprit of falling short by little margins before tonight but they have managed to silence a lot of their critics. They were relentless. They never took off the pedal barring a few overs from Narine. Third win for PBKS and they are still in the fray. KKR stay at number 2 but the confidence of their bowlers would have been hit for sure. This will be a tough pill to swallow. We will need sleeping pills to mellow down our nerves. Our team of Pradeep Krishnamurthy, Akshay Maanay, Praveen Kumar and Kumar Abhisekh Das bid you bye bye
